96
00:08:06,970 --> 00:08:09,560
I don't mind you treasuring your kind,

97
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:15,220
but losing a fight while holding back your true strength is a disgrace to the Yato.

98
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:21,560
Your love for the Yato blood has lead you to behave in a way shameful to the Yato.

99
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:23,580
Like I said.

100
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:25,860
I have no interest in the weak.

101
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:30,620
I don't recall holding myself back.

102
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:37,840
Though I can't deny feeling that it would be a waste to end such talent in a place like this.

103
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:42,520
It was the same way I felt when I met you, captain.

104
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:45,470
You siblings fascinate me.

105
00:08:46,570 --> 00:08:48,140
I'm very happy.

106
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:50,810
Promising youngsters coming one after another.

107
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:53,260
We've got a bright future ahead of us.

108
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:57,220
This is your era now.

109
00:08:57,220 --> 00:09:11,940
[This is a reference to the Japanese myth of rabbits living on the moon pounding mochi.]

110
00:08:57,220 --> 00:09:02,390
Us old bunnies will be returning to the moon with the King of the Night.

111
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:11,940
Say?

112
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:14,110
What's going on here?

113
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:15,670
Abuto.

114
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,430
I felt the same way you did.

115
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:21,220
I became curious of a man's future and couldn't kill him.

116
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:27,340
A man who is truly strong is strong in both body and soul.

117
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:30,520
This man was far from that.

118
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:35,730
He had a fragile body and a weak soul bound by worthless beliefs.

119
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,890
Yet that man was able to defeat the King of the Night.

120
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:42,880
Standing every time he was crushed...

121
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,310
Overcoming impossible odds...

122
00:09:45,310 --> 00:09:47,600
And in the end, he survived on the battlefield.

123
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,850
Interesting, isn't it?

124
00:09:52,850 --> 00:09:54,730
The universe sure is a big place.

125
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:58,160
