132
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:25,300
Our superiors won't keep quiet once they find out about the changes in Yoshiwara.

133
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:29,020
Which means those guys won't get away easily.

134
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,810
I'm not very good at negotiating my way through this world.

135
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:35,810
Abuto, I still need you to stay alive.

136
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:42,140
So come up with a way to keep our superiors and let the samurai live?

137
00:10:43,890 --> 00:10:46,500
Hey, you gotta be kidding me.

138
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:50,840
Why do I have to work so hard for the sake of some barbarian

139
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:53,100
on this remote planet who isn't one of us?

140
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:55,540
Because you're the one who said

141
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:58,660
that you would open the way to becoming the Pirate King of the universe.

142
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:00,700
That's different.

143
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:02,500
Hey, are you listening?

144
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,360
Hey, you bonehead!

145
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:09,690
Kamui, you will eventually learn.

146
00:11:09,690 --> 00:11:14,940
When you're old and look back at the path you took,

147
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:18,500
you'll find that our path is empty.

148
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:21,370
Boss, that's fine with me.

149
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:23,370
There isn't anything I want.

150
00:11:23,770 --> 00:11:25,350
There isn't any reason for me to look back.

151
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:27,510
I only see what's ahead.

152
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:31,540
A new battlefield spreading before my eyes...

153
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:33,830
That is what I seek.

154
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,830
I strive to become stronger than any other person.

155
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,790
I move forward to become stronger than anything.

156
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:44,670
Even if I have nothing left to protect when I get there.

157
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:06,190
You've found an unbearably hot place to rest.

158
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:10,330
Serves you right, Hosen.

159
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,830
The prostitutes...

160
00:12:12,830 --> 00:12:15,680
They wanted to let him sunbathe in the afterlife.

161
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,060
So? What do you want?

162
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:23,760
Was he a pal of yours?

163
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:25,520
Sorry about that.

164
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:29,770
No, it's just that the more annoying they are...

165
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:34,100
So maybe I'll be attending your funeral as well.

166
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,330
Aren't you happy?

167
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:36,790
No, I'll be attending yours.

168
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,610
And making frequent visits.

169
00:12:37,610 --> 00:12:39,470
No, I can top that.

170
00:12:39,470 --> 00:12:40,640
I'll use a jet to visit you.

171
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,580
No. My jet is faster.

172
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:44,970
No, my jet has cheaper flights.

173
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:52,370
It seems you're as crazy as ever.

174
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:55,520
I didn't expect you to take down Hosen.

175
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,840
Want to try me, the Umi Bozu, next?

176
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,390
That's not funny.

177
00:13:00,390 --> 00:13:03,080
