264
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:47,420
Somebody's choosing to be chained up right here!

265
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:48,380
Hey!

266
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:50,300
Is Seita-kun really okay here?!

267
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,730
He's living a normal life, right?!

268
00:17:52,730 --> 00:17:55,450
Yeah. Seita's fine.

269
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:59,560
He's staying with Hinowa and working at a toy store.

270
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,530
Whew... That's a relief.

271
00:18:01,530 --> 00:18:03,220
At least there's a store for kids around here.

272
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:05,430
That's just an XXX store?!

273
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:05,430
[Adult Toy Store]

274
00:18:05,430 --> 00:18:09,090
Sorry, I'd already expected something like this when I heard the words "toy store."

275
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:10,700
I totally saw this coming, you know?!

276
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:11,810
I see.

277
00:18:11,810 --> 00:18:13,440
I'll work harder on the next one.

278
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,790
You don't have to!

279
00:18:14,790 --> 00:18:15,640
Are you playing dumb?!

280
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:16,710
Are you making fun of me?!

281
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:18,490
Gin-san! Everyone!

282
00:18:18,490 --> 00:18:19,680
Long time no see!

283
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:22,930
You! Stop running towards us sounding like a mobile suit!

284
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:24,930
I've missed you, everyone!

285
00:18:25,150 --> 00:18:26,850
I'm going to work hard in this town...

286
00:18:38,930 --> 00:18:40,970
What's the big idea, brat?!

287
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:42,380
Tsukuyo-san, help!

288
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:43,760
We've got a problem!

289
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,670
Gah! Where're you aiming at?!

290
00:18:45,670 --> 00:18:47,500
Outta the way, four-eyes!

291
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:51,060
Give me back my first time!

292
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:55,770
So what do you think of our town?

293
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:02,460
It's just like some other town.

294
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:04,000
Yeah.

295
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,500
It's just like ours.

296
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,970
Vulgar and brutal...

297
00:19:08,970 --> 00:19:11,310
Gentle and cold...

298
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:13,600
Smiles and tears...

299
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,800
And you've got the sun.

300
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,890
Just a normal town.

301
00:19:24,170 --> 00:19:25,660
Isn't it wonderful?

302
00:22:47,370 --> 00:22:50,340
[Yoshiwara is Burning]

303
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:52,790
[Fin]

304
00:23:12,820 --> 00:23:15,470
...It's great.

305
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:22,060
[Ask Mr. Ginpachi!!]

306
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:22,400
Ask Mr. Ginpachi!

307
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,750
Uh...

308
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:27,050
We have a question from pen name "Off-season Thunderdome."

309
00:23:27,050 --> 00:23:32,390
"When Kagura's older brother Kamui showed up during a flashback in episode 42, a couple years ago,

310
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:37,680
and also when you could see him from behind in a previous ending sequence, I believe his hair was black.

311
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,980
What is going on here?

312
00:23:39,980 --> 00:23:41,770
Was I just imagining things?"

313
00:23:44,730 --> 00:23:46,510
You weren't.

314
00:23:46,810 --> 00:23:48,810
[Rejected]

315
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:53,780
Uh...The next one is from pen name "Rectal Punch from Hell."

316
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:58,420
During the "Yoshiwara Is Burning" arc,
which part of Yoshiwara was burning?

317
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:05,020
[Rejected]

318
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:05,020
[The End]

319
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:14,270
[Preview]

320
00:24:06,020 --> 00:24:10,130
After the end of this long battle,
we had only one thought...

321
00:24:10,130 --> 00:24:11,270
Yes...

322
00:24:11,270 --> 00:24:13,810
We want to become stronger!

323
00:24:14,570 --> 00:24:15,370
The next episode:

324
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:19,260
"All Adults are Instructors for All Children."

325
00:24:20,020 --> 00:24:25,890
[People who are further along on their quest for strength than Shinpachi and Kagura appear.]

326
00:24:25,890 --> 00:24:29,930
[Starting next week, it's back to business as usual at Odd Jobs Gin.]

327
00:24:29,930 --> 00:24:35,010
[See you next time.]
